# 4. Work Metadata

Describe la obra como entidad base.

```json
{
  "workId": "les_miserables_victor_hugo_1862",
  "title": "Les Misérables",
  "author": "Victor Hugo",
  "year": 1862,
  "sourceType": "public_domain",
  "language": "fr",
  "availableLocales": ["en", "es"],
  "categories": ["classic", "social", "moral", "historical"],
  "premise": "A man pursued by the law struggles to redeem his life through compassion and sacrifice."
}
```

Campos clave:

* `workId`: identificador único
* `sourceType`: public_domain, original_user_content, licensed
* `premise`: resumen abstracto, no copia literal
* `categories`: útil para filtros en web

---

# 5. World Model

Representa las reglas del mundo narrativo.

```json
{
  "worldModel": {
    "setting": {
      "timePeriod": "19th_century",
      "locations": ["Paris", "France"],
      "socialContext": ["poverty", "justice_system", "class_inequality"]
    },
    "worldRules": [
      "The legal system is rigid and punitive.",
      "Social mobility is limited.",
      "Compassion can radically alter human destiny."
    ],
    "tone": ["tragic", "hopeful", "moral"],
    "stakes": ["freedom", "identity", "redemption", "survival"]
  }
}
```

Esto le permite al motor saber qué puede cambiar y qué define la identidad del mundo.

---

# 6. Character Model

Cada personaje debe existir como entidad funcional, no solo como nombre.

```json
{
  "characters": [
    {
      "characterId": "jean_valjean",
      "name": "Jean Valjean",
      "role": "protagonist",
      "archetype": "redeemed_outcast",
      "coreDrives": ["survival", "redemption", "protection"],
      "fears": ["capture", "moral_failure"],
      "initialState": {
        "socialStatus": "criminalized",
        "moralState": "conflicted",
        "resources": "low"
      },
      "relationships": [
        {
          "targetCharacterId": "javert",
          "relationshipType": "pursuer_vs_pursued",
          "tensionLevel": 10
        },
        {
          "targetCharacterId": "cosette",
          "relationshipType": "protector",
          "tensionLevel": 2
        }
      ],
      "changeCapacity": "high"
    }
  ]
}
```

Campos importantes:

* `archetype`: útil para abstracción
* `coreDrives`: qué mueve al personaje
* `initialState`: punto de inicio
* `relationships`: clave para cambios sistémicos
* `changeCapacity`: cuánto puede transformarse sin romper coherencia

---

# 7. Narrative Variables

Este es el corazón de byDebut.

Cada obra debe tener variables manipulables.

```json
{
  "narrativeVariables": [
    {
      "variableId": "mercy_received",
      "label": "Receives mercy early",
      "description": "Whether the protagonist receives unexpected compassion at a key turning point.",
      "type": "boolean",
      "defaultValue": true,
      "impactScope": ["character_arc", "moral_tone", "ending"],
      "sensitivity": "high"
    },
    {
      "variableId": "law_rigidity",
      "label": "Rigidity of the law",
      "description": "How flexible or unforgiving the justice system is.",
      "type": "enum",
      "allowedValues": ["low", "medium", "high"],
      "defaultValue": "high",
      "impactScope": ["world_conflict", "pacing", "ending"],
      "sensitivity": "high"
    },
    {
      "variableId": "guardian_bond_strength",
      "label": "Strength of protective bond",
      "description": "How strongly the protagonist commits to protecting another character.",
      "type": "scale",
      "min": 1,
      "max": 10,
      "defaultValue": 9,
      "impactScope": ["character_arc", "relationship_arc"],
      "sensitivity": "medium"
    }
  ]
}
```

Tipos recomendados:

* `boolean`
* `enum`
* `scale`
* `text_constraint`
* `conditional_toggle`

Cada variable debe indicar:

* valor por defecto
* alcance del impacto
* sensibilidad narrativa

