# 8. Decision Graph

Mapea los puntos donde una decisión cambia el sistema.

```json
{
  "decisionGraph": {
    "nodes": [
      {
        "nodeId": "inciting_incident",
        "label": "Initial crisis",
        "type": "event",
        "dependsOn": []
      },
      {
        "nodeId": "moral_turning_point",
        "label": "Moral turning point",
        "type": "decision",
        "dependsOn": ["inciting_incident"],
        "affectedByVariables": ["mercy_received"]
      },
      {
        "nodeId": "conflict_escalation",
        "label": "Conflict escalation",
        "type": "event",
        "dependsOn": ["moral_turning_point"],
        "affectedByVariables": ["law_rigidity", "guardian_bond_strength"]
      },
      {
        "nodeId": "ending_resolution",
        "label": "Ending resolution",
        "type": "resolution",
        "dependsOn": ["conflict_escalation"]
      }
    ],
    "edges": [
      {
        "from": "inciting_incident",
        "to": "moral_turning_point"
      },
      {
        "from": "moral_turning_point",
        "to": "conflict_escalation"
      },
      {
        "from": "conflict_escalation",
        "to": "ending_resolution"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Esto permite:

* comparar versiones
* ver dónde cambió la historia
* explicar causalidad al usuario

