# 16. Ejemplo real: Hamlet

```json
{
  "workId": "hamlet_shakespeare",
  "title": "Hamlet",
  "premise": "A grieving prince must decide whether to act against corruption.",
  "narrativeVariables": [
    {
      "variableId": "hesitation_level",
      "label": "Hamlet hesitation",
      "type": "scale",
      "min": 1,
      "max": 10,
      "defaultValue": 10
    },
    {
      "variableId": "ghost_reliability",
      "label": "Reliability of the ghost",
      "type": "enum",
      "allowedValues": ["uncertain", "credible", "deceptive"],
      "defaultValue": "uncertain"
    }
  ],
  "decisionGraph": {
    "nodes": [
      { "nodeId": "ghost_message", "type": "event" },
      { "nodeId": "hamlet_doubt", "type": "decision" },
      { "nodeId": "public_action", "type": "decision" },
      { "nodeId": "court_collapse", "type": "resolution" }
    ]
  }
}
```

Ejemplo de cambio:

* `hesitation_level = 2`
* resultado: Hamlet actúa antes, reduce intriga interna, acelera colapso político, cambia tono y final.

